        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 10 at 2:21PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 221 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Clayton, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Clayton.

This includes Highway 64 between Mile Markers 425 and 429.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
